main event: A civilian reported seeing two bright silvery objects in the sky for several hours on 19 July 1966.
interesting points: The observation lasted several hours and included sightings of lights resembling moving stars or planets., The objects were observed at various degrees of azimuth and elevation, thought to be planets like Patoria and Aldebaran., There was no photographic evidence or reports of other sightings from aircraft in the area during that time., The observer was a waitress in a snack bar located in Del Paso Heights., Weather conditions were clear and visibility was good during the observation period.
witness description: Miss California, waitress in a Snack Bar
